President Biden provided an update on his plan to combat COVID-19 and discussed the progress being made in the fight against the virus. He highlighted that nationally, daily cases and hospitalizations are decreasing, and vaccination rates are increasing. The President emphasized the need to vaccinate the remaining unvaccinated population and announced that the Labor Department will soon issue an emergency rule requiring vaccination for companies with 100 or more employees. He also addressed misinformation surrounding vaccine requirements and commended businesses and organizations that have implemented such requirements. The President mentioned that the FDA is reviewing data on Moderna and Johnson & Johnson boosters and expects a decision in the next few weeks. He encouraged the continuation of safety measures in schools and expressed readiness for vaccinating children aged 5 to 11 once authorized. President Biden concluded by urging businesses, parents, and unvaccinated individuals to take action in order to defeat the pandemic and drive economic recovery.